From: FlareSolverr Stealth Migration
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] Add window bounds offset to CDP mouse screenX/screenY

CDP mouse events use raw coordinates as screenX/screenY, ignoring
the browser window's position on the virtual display. This creates
an impossible screen < viewport combination that fingerprinters flag.
Add the window container bounds offset so screen coordinates are correct.

--- a/content/browser/devtools/protocol/input_handler.cc
+++ b/content/browser/devtools/protocol/input_handler.cc
@@ -200,6 +200,8 @@ Response InputHandler::DispatchMouseEvent(
       web_contents_->GetPrimaryMainFrame()->GetView();
   gfx::PointF screen_point(x, y);
+  gfx::Rect window_bounds = web_contents_->GetContainerBounds();
+  screen_point.Offset(window_bounds.x(), window_bounds.y());
   if (web_view) {
     screen_point = web_view->TransformRootPointToScreenCoordF(screen_point);
   }
